==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}} 
# Strong desire, especially of a sexual nature
#: ''Upon seeing her, I was filled with '''lust'''''

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# To very strongly desire.
# To want to have sexual intercourse with.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /lʌst/, /lʊst/
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ʌst|-ʌst]]

===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*lust-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian ''lust'', Old High German ''lust'' (German [[lust#German|lust]]), Old Norse [[losti]], Gothic.

